---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { forgeUrl, githubOrgUrl, marketUrl } from '../data/products';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Contribute"
  description="AgentKitProject is open-core. Here's how to contribute code, kits, docs, and feedback."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open-core</p>
      <h1>AgentKitProject is open-core — contributions welcome.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The public monorepo, the core kit engine, and the CLI are open source. The project is
        built around open ecosystem, local-first, and no-vendor-lock-in principles, with both
        hosted and self-hosted support — contributions of code, kits, docs, and feedback all help.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={githubOrgUrl}>View GitHub organization</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={forgeUrl}>Start with Forge</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container grid three">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Code</h3>
        <p>
          The public <code>agentkit</code> monorepo holds the web apps (<code>apps/*</code>) and
          the shared libraries (<code>packages/*</code>), including the
          <code>@agentkitforge/core</code> kit engine and the <code>agentkitforge</code> CLI.
          Open an issue or a pull request on GitHub.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Build &amp; share Agent Kits</h3>
        <p>
          Create Agent Kits with Forge or the CLI, then publish them to AgentKitMarket so other
          people can discover and use them.
        </p>
        <p><a href={marketUrl}>Open AgentKitMarket</a></p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Docs &amp; feedback</h3>
        <p>
          Improve documentation, report bugs, or request features through GitHub issues on the
          monorepo.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Self-host &amp; report back</h3>
        <p>
          The stack is fully self-hostable and open-core. Run it on your own infrastructure and
          share feedback or fixes from what you find.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="content-panel">
        <h2>Get started on GitHub.</h2>
        <p>
          Issues, pull requests, and discussion all happen in the open on the AgentKitProject
          GitHub organization.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button" href={githubOrgUrl}>View GitHub organization</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
